⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Sabin Rene Figaro
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦Sabin Rene Figaro:FF6:54bfdb⟧

WHO   — Sabin Rene Figaro — the renegade prince
WHAT  — The Blitz-fighting monk of Final Fantasy VI — a towering, gentle-hearted giant who fights with nothing but his own flesh and learned will, and who famously caught a runaway Phantom Train and suplexed it off the rails.
WHERE — FF6 · Final Fantasy VI  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI (America's Final Fantasy III, 1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a man should be free to choose his own road; because strength of body is meaningless without a good heart to steer it; because loyalty to a brother and a broken world is worth more than any inherited title.
HOW   — By raw martial discipline — the Blitz techniques drilled into muscle and breath — by a child's stubborn refusal to be caged by duty, and by a kindness that makes his enormous strength a shield for others rather than a weapon over them.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I flipped a coin and chose the road over the crown — and I'll meet whatever comes with my own two hands.

spoken token : seirn-laex-gror   ·   hex : 54bfdb
